# JaegerWhisperSTT

The `stt`-slot engine module for the [Jaeger ecosystem](https://github.com/Jenkins-Robotics/JaegerOS) — a pywhispercpp-backed speech-to-text engine plugging into [JaegerOS](https://github.com/Jenkins-Robotics/JaegerOS)'s module/slot system.

Pins `jaeger-os` only — never `jaeger-ai` — so a robot body (JP01 and
friends) can listen without the AI product installed at all. Two real
consumers today: the [JaegerAI](https://github.com/Jenkins-Robotics/JaegerAI)
product and the JP01 non-AI console.

See `jaeger_whisper_stt/nodes/whisper_stt/__init__.py` and
`module.yaml` for the module contract (slot, topics, tools, factory,
`requires_libraries`). For the ecosystem-wide picture (Mind / Body /
Soul, module discovery, the three-tier structure), see JaegerOS's
`dev/docs/vision/THREE_TIER_STRUCTURE.md` — canonical there, linked
from here rather than duplicated.

## Install (editable, staging)

```
pip install -e .
```

Expects a sibling `../JaegerOS` clone (see `requirements.txt`) until
`jaeger-os` has published releases.

## Tests

```
pytest
```
